genresAdvancedInfo.name: rondalla
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Rondalla is a traditional music genre from the Philippines that originated in the Spanish colonial era. It is characterized by its use of plucked string instruments, such as the bandurria and laud, and features both vocal and instrumental music. Rondalla is often performed during social events and celebrations and has become an integral part of Filipino cultural heritage.
